        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer434348959" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11874088205302305892">I wanted a light, well written book &amp; this is exactly what I got.<br/><br/>I have always enjoyed the historical context of the civil war between Stephen &amp; Maude in the 1100&apos;s &amp; this particular novel advanced that knowledge as it becomes specifically entwined in the plot.<br/><br/>I was correct in my deductions, but I could also see how it would be a surprise as the important reason for the crime is not bleedingly obvious - which also stumped Cadfaedel as well.</span>
  <span id="freeText11874088205302305892" style="display:none">I wanted a light, well written book &amp; this is exactly what I got.<br /><br />I have always enjoyed the historical context of the civil war between Stephen &amp; Maude in the 1100's &amp; this particular novel advanced that knowledge as it becomes specifically entwined in the plot.<br /><br />I was correct in my deductions, but I could also see how it would be a surprise as the important reason for the crime is not bleedingly obvious - which also stumped Cadfaedel as well.</span>
